@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@organizationId = 1
@taskId = 1
@userBId = 2

### Use this file manually:
### 1. Run login first.
### 2. Copy the accessToken from the login response.
### 3. Paste it into the Authorization header as Bearer <token>.

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Database Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health/db

### Register User A
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "User A",
  "email": "usera@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### Register User B
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "User B",
  "email": "userb@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

